benchmarks.name: Recursive Fibonacci

benchmarks.logos_source:
## To native args () -> Seq of Text
## To native parseInt (s: Text) -> Int

## To fib (n: Int) -> Int:
    If n is less than 2:
        Return n.
    Return fib(n - 1) + fib(n - 2).

## Main
Let arguments be args().
Let n be parseInt(item 2 of arguments).
Show fib(n).

benchmarks.name: Ackermann Function
benchmarks.description: Ackermann(3, m). Measures extreme recursion depth and stack frame overhead.
benchmarks.logos_source:
## To native args () -> Seq of Text
## To native parseInt (s: Text) -> Int

## To ackermann (m: Int) and (n: Int) -> Int:
    If m equals 0:
        Return n + 1.
    If n equals 0:
        Return ackermann(m - 1, 1).
    Return ackermann(m - 1, ackermann(m, n - 1)).

## Main
Let arguments be args().
Let n be parseInt(item 2 of arguments).
Show ackermann(3, n).

benchmarks.name: N-Queens
benchmarks.description: N-Queens backtracking. Measures recursive constraint solving.
benchmarks.logos_source:
## To native args () -> Seq of Text
## To native parseInt (s: Text) -> Int

## To solve (row: Int, cols: Int, diag1: Int, diag2: Int, n: Int) -> Int:
    If row equals n:
        Return 1.
    Let all be (1 shifted left by n) - 1.
    Let mutable available be all and not (cols or diag1 or diag2).
    Let mutable count be 0.
    While available is not 0:
        Let bit be available and (0 - available).
        Set available to available xor bit.
        Set count to count + solve(row + 1, cols or bit, (diag1 or bit) shifted left by 1, (diag2 or bit) shifted right by 1, n).
    Return count.

## Main
Let arguments be args().
Let n be parseInt(item 2 of arguments).
Show solve(0, 0, 0, 0, n).

benchmarks.name: Bubble Sort
benchmarks.description: O(n^2) bubble sort. Measures nested loops, indexed array mutation, and swap patterns.
benchmarks.logos_source:
## To native args () -> Seq of Text
## To native parseInt (s: Text) -> Int

## Main
Let arguments be args().
Let n be parseInt(item 2 of arguments).
Let mutable arr be a new Seq of Int.
Let mutable seed be 42.
Let mutable i be 0.
While i is less than n:
    Set seed to (seed * 1103515245 + 12345) % 4294967296.
    Push (seed / 65536) % 32768 to arr.
    Set i to i + 1.
Set i to 0.
While i is less than n - 1:
    Let mutable j be 1.
    While j is at most n - 1 - i:
        Let a be item j of arr.
        Let b be item (j + 1) of arr.
        If a is greater than b:
            Set item j of arr to b.
            Set item (j + 1) of arr to a.
        Set j to j + 1.
    Set i to i + 1.
Show item 1 of arr.

benchmarks.name: Merge Sort
benchmarks.description: Top-down merge sort. Measures allocation-heavy divide-and-conquer.
benchmarks.logos_source:
## To native args () -> Seq of Text
## To native parseInt (s: Text) -> Int

## To mergeSort (arr: Seq of Int) -> Seq of Int:
    Let n be length of arr.
    If n is less than 2:
        Return arr.
    Let mid be n / 2.
    Let mutable left be a new Seq of Int.
    Let mutable right be a new Seq of Int.
    Let mutable i be 1.
    While i is at most mid:
        Push item i of arr to left.
        Set i to i + 1.
    While i is at most n:
        Push item i of arr to right.
        Set i to i + 1.
    Set left to mergeSort(left).
    Set right to mergeSort(right).
    Let mutable result be a new Seq of Int.
    Let mutable li be 1.
    Let mutable ri be 1.
    While li is at most length of left:
        If ri is greater than length of right:
            Push item li of left to result.
            Set li to li + 1.
        Otherwise:
            If item li of left is at most item ri of right:
                Push item li of left to result.
                Set li to li + 1.
            Otherwise:
                Push item ri of right to result.
                Set ri to ri + 1.
    While ri is at most length of right:
        Push item ri of right to result.
        Set ri to ri + 1.
    Return result.

## Main
Let arguments be args().
Let n be parseInt(item 2 of arguments).
Let mutable arr be a new Seq of Int.
Let mutable seed be 42.
Let mutable i be 0.
While i is less than n:
    Set seed to (seed * 1103515245 + 12345) % 2147483648.
    Push (seed / 65536) % 32768 to arr.
    Set i to i + 1.
Set arr to mergeSort(arr).
Let mutable checksum be 0.
Set i to 1.
While i is at most n:
    Set checksum to (checksum + item i of arr) % 1000000007.
    Set i to i + 1.
Show "" + item 1 of arr + " " + item n of arr + " " + checksum.

benchmarks.name: Quicksort
benchmarks.description: Lomuto-partition quicksort. Measures in-place swap-heavy recursion.
benchmarks.logos_source:
## To native args () -> Seq of Text
## To native parseInt (s: Text) -> Int

## To qs (arr: Seq of Int, lo: Int, hi: Int) -> Seq of Int:
    If lo is at least hi:
        Return arr.
    Let pivot be item hi of arr.
    Let mutable result be arr.
    Let mutable i be lo.
    Let mutable j be lo.
    While j is less than hi:
        If item j of result is at most pivot:
            Let tmp be item i of result.
            Set item i of result to item j of result.
            Set item j of result to tmp.
            Set i to i + 1.
        Set j to j + 1.
    Let tmp be item i of result.
    Set item i of result to item hi of result.
    Set item hi of result to tmp.
    Set result to qs(result, lo, i - 1).
    Set result to qs(result, i + 1, hi).
    Return result.

## Main
Let arguments be args().
Let n be parseInt(item 2 of arguments).
Let mutable arr be a new Seq of Int.
Let mutable seed be 42.
Let mutable i be 0.
While i is less than n:
    Set seed to (seed * 1103515245 + 12345) % 2147483648.
    Push (seed / 65536) % 32768 to arr.
    Set i to i + 1.
Set arr to qs(arr, 1, n).
Let mutable checksum be 0.
Set i to 1.
While i is at most n:
    Set checksum to (checksum + item i of arr) % 1000000007.
    Set i to i + 1.
Show "" + item 1 of arr + " " + item n of arr + " " + checksum.

benchmarks.name: Counting Sort
benchmarks.description: Non-comparison O(n+k) sort. Measures pure array indexing throughput.
benchmarks.logos_source:
## To native args () -> Seq of Text
## To native parseInt (s: Text) -> Int

## Main
Let arguments be args().
Let n be parseInt(item 2 of arguments).
Let mutable arr be a new Seq of Int.
Let mutable seed be 42.
Let mutable i be 0.
While i is less than n:
    Set seed to (seed * 1103515245 + 12345) % 2147483648.
    Push (seed / 65536) % 1000 to arr.
    Set i to i + 1.
Let mutable counts be a new Seq of Int.
Set i to 0.
While i is less than 1000:
    Push 0 to counts.
    Set i to i + 1.
Set i to 1.
While i is at most n:
    Let v be item i of arr.
    Set item (v + 1) of counts to (item (v + 1) of counts) + 1.
    Set i to i + 1.
Let mutable sorted be a new Seq of Int.
Let mutable v be 0.
While v is less than 1000:
    Let mutable c be 0.
    While c is less than item (v + 1) of counts:
        Push v to sorted.
        Set c to c + 1.
    Set v to v + 1.
Let mutable checksum be 0.
Set i to 1.
While i is at most n:
    Set checksum to (checksum + item i of sorted) % 1000000007.
    Set i to i + 1.
Show "" + item 1 of sorted + " " + item n of sorted + " " + checksum.

benchmarks.name: Heap Sort
benchmarks.description: Heap sort with sift-down. Measures logarithmic array jumps.
benchmarks.logos_source:
## To native args () -> Seq of Text
## To native parseInt (s: Text) -> Int

## To siftDown (arr: Seq of Int, start: Int, end: Int) -> Seq of Int:
    Let mutable result be arr.
    Let mutable root be start.
    While 2 * root + 1 is at most end:
        Let child be 2 * root + 1.
        Let mutable swapIdx be root.
        If item (swapIdx + 1) of result is less than item (child + 1) of result:
            Set swapIdx to child.
        If child + 1 is at most end:
            If item (swapIdx + 1) of result is less than item (child + 2) of result:
                Set swapIdx to child + 1.
        If swapIdx equals root:
            Return result.
        Let tmp be item (root + 1) of result.
        Set item (root + 1) of result to item (swapIdx + 1) of result.
        Set item (swapIdx + 1) of result to tmp.
        Set root to swapIdx.
    Return result.

## Main
Let arguments be args().
Let n be parseInt(item 2 of arguments).
Let mutable arr be a new Seq of Int.
Let mutable seed be 42.
Let mutable i be 0.
While i is less than n:
    Set seed to (seed * 1103515245 + 12345) % 2147483648.
    Push (seed / 65536) % 32768 to arr.
    Set i to i + 1.
Let mutable start be (n - 2) / 2.
While start is at least 0:
    Set arr to siftDown(arr, start, n - 1).
    Set start to start - 1.
Let mutable end be n - 1.
While end is greater than 0:
    Let tmp be item 1 of arr.
    Set item 1 of arr to item (end + 1) of arr.
    Set item (end + 1) of arr to tmp.
    Set end to end - 1.
    Set arr to siftDown(arr, 0, end).
Let mutable checksum be 0.
Set i to 1.
While i is at most n:
    Set checksum to (checksum + item i of arr) % 1000000007.
    Set i to i + 1.
Show "" + item 1 of arr + " " + item n of arr + " " + checksum.

benchmarks.name: N-Body Simulation
benchmarks.description: 5-body gravitational simulation. Measures FP struct arrays and sqrt.
benchmarks.logos_source:
## To native args () -> Seq of Text
## To native parseInt (s: Text) -> Int

## Main
Let arguments be args().
Let n be parseInt(item 2 of arguments).
Let pi be 3.141592653589793.
Let solarMass be 4.0 * pi * pi.
Let daysPerYear be 365.24.

Let mutable bx be a new Seq of Float.
Let mutable posY be a new Seq of Float.
Let mutable bz be a new Seq of Float.
Let mutable bvx be a new Seq of Float.
Let mutable bvy be a new Seq of Float.
Let mutable bvz be a new Seq of Float.
Let mutable bm be a new Seq of Float.

Push 0.0 to bx. Push 0.0 to posY. Push 0.0 to bz.
Push 0.0 to bvx. Push 0.0 to bvy. Push 0.0 to bvz.
Push solarMass to bm.

Push 4.841431442464721 to bx. Push 0.0 - 1.1603200440274284 to posY. Push 0.0 - 0.10362204447112311 to bz.
Push 0.001660076642744037 * daysPerYear to bvx. Push 0.007699011184197404 * daysPerYear to bvy. Push 0.0 - 0.0000690460016972063 * daysPerYear to bvz.
Push 0.0009547919384243266 * solarMass to bm.

Push 8.34336671824458 to bx. Push 4.124798564124305 to posY. Push 0.0 - 0.4035234171143214 to bz.
Push 0.0 - 0.002767425107268624 * daysPerYear to bvx. Push 0.004998528012349172 * daysPerYear to bvy. Push 0.00002304172975737639 * daysPerYear to bvz.
Push 0.0002858859806661308 * solarMass to bm.

Push 12.894369562139131 to bx. Push 0.0 - 15.111151401698631 to posY. Push 0.0 - 0.22330757889265573 to bz.
Push 0.002964601375647616 * daysPerYear to bvx. Push 0.0023784717395948095 * daysPerYear to bvy. Push 0.0 - 0.000029658956854023756 * daysPerYear to bvz.
Push 0.00004366244043351563 * solarMass to bm.

Push 15.379697114850917 to bx. Push 0.0 - 25.919314609987964 to posY. Push 0.17925877295037118 to bz.
Push 0.0026806777249038932 * daysPerYear to bvx. Push 0.001628241700382423 * daysPerYear to bvy. Push 0.0 - 0.00009515922545197159 * daysPerYear to bvz.
Push 0.00005151389020466114 * solarMass to bm.

Let mutable px be 0.0.
Let mutable py be 0.0.
Let mutable pz be 0.0.
Let mutable i be 1.
While i is at most 5:
    Set px to px + item i of bvx * item i of bm.
    Set py to py + item i of bvy * item i of bm.
    Set pz to pz + item i of bvz * item i of bm.
    Set i to i + 1.
Set item 1 of bvx to 0.0 - px / solarMass.
Set item 1 of bvy to 0.0 - py / solarMass.
Set item 1 of bvz to 0.0 - pz / solarMass.

Let mutable e be 0.0.
Set i to 1.
While i is at most 5:
    Set e to e + 0.5 * item i of bm * (item i of bvx * item i of bvx + item i of bvy * item i of bvy + item i of bvz * item i of bvz).
    Let mutable j be i + 1.
    While j is at most 5:
        Let dx be item i of bx - item j of bx.
        Let dy be item i of posY - item j of posY.
        Let dz be item i of bz - item j of bz.
        Set e to e - item i of bm * item j of bm / sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy + dz * dz).
        Set j to j + 1.
    Set i to i + 1.
Show "{e:.9}".

Let dt be 0.01.
Let mutable step be 0.
While step is less than n:
    Set i to 1.
    While i is at most 5:
        Let mutable j be i + 1.
        While j is at most 5:
            Let dx be item i of bx - item j of bx.
            Let dy be item i of posY - item j of posY.
            Let dz be item i of bz - item j of bz.
            Let dist be sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy + dz * dz).
            Let mag be dt / (dist * dist * dist).
            Set item i of bvx to item i of bvx - dx * item j of bm * mag.
            Set item i of bvy to item i of bvy - dy * item j of bm * mag.
            Set item i of bvz to item i of bvz - dz * item j of bm * mag.
            Set item j of bvx to item j of bvx + dx * item i of bm * mag.
            Set item j of bvy to item j of bvy + dy * item i of bm * mag.
            Set item j of bvz to item j of bvz + dz * item i of bm * mag.
            Set j to j + 1.
        Set i to i + 1.
    Set i to 1.
    While i is at most 5:
        Set item i of bx to item i of bx + dt * item i of bvx.
        Set item i of posY to item i of posY + dt * item i of bvy.
        Set item i of bz to item i of bz + dt * item i of bvz.
        Set i to i + 1.
    Set step to step + 1.

Set e to 0.0.
Set i to 1.
While i is at most 5:
    Set e to e + 0.5 * item i of bm * (item i of bvx * item i of bvx + item i of bvy * item i of bvy + item i of bvz * item i of bvz).
    Let mutable j be i + 1.
    While j is at most 5:
        Let dx be item i of bx - item j of bx.
        Let dy be item i of posY - item j of posY.
        Let dz be item i of bz - item j of bz.
        Set e to e - item i of bm * item j of bm / sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy + dz * dz).
        Set j to j + 1.
    Set i to i + 1.
Show "{e:.9}".

benchmarks.name: Mandelbrot Set
benchmarks.description: Mandelbrot set escape iteration. Measures FP branching and convergence.
benchmarks.logos_source:
## To native args () -> Seq of Text
## To native parseInt (s: Text) -> Int

## Main
Let arguments be args().
Let n be parseInt(item 2 of arguments).
Let mutable count be 0.
Let mutable y be 0.
While y is less than n:
    Let mutable x be 0.
    While x is less than n:
        Let cr be 2.0 * x / n - 1.5.
        Let ci be 2.0 * y / n - 1.0.
        Let mutable zr be 0.0.
        Let mutable zi be 0.0.
        Let mutable isInside be 1.
        Let mutable iter be 0.
        While iter is less than 50:
            Let zr2 be zr * zr - zi * zi + cr.
            Let zi2 be 2.0 * zr * zi + ci.
            Set zr to zr2.
            Set zi to zi2.
            If zr * zr + zi * zi is greater than 4.0:
                Set isInside to 0.
                Set iter to 50.
            Set iter to iter + 1.
        If isInside equals 1:
            Set count to count + 1.
        Set x to x + 1.
    Set y to y + 1.
Show count.

benchmarks.name: Spectral Norm
benchmarks.description: Spectral norm power method. Measures FP dot products and array throughput.
benchmarks.logos_source:
## To native args () -> Seq of Text
## To native parseInt (s: Text) -> Int

## To aVal (i: Int, j: Int) -> Float:
    Return 1.0 / ((i + j) * (i + j + 1) / 2 + i + 1).

## To mulAv (n: Int, v: Seq of Float, out: Seq of Float) -> Seq of Float:
    Let mutable result be out.
    Let mutable i be 0.
    While i is less than n:
        Let mutable sum be 0.0.
        Let mutable j be 0.
        While j is less than n:
            Set sum to sum + aVal(i, j) * item (j + 1) of v.
            Set j to j + 1.
        Set item (i + 1) of result to sum.
        Set i to i + 1.
    Return result.

## To mulAtv (n: Int, v: Seq of Float, out: Seq of Float) -> Seq of Float:
    Let mutable result be out.
    Let mutable i be 0.
    While i is less than n:
        Let mutable sum be 0.0.
        Let mutable j be 0.
        While j is less than n:
            Set sum to sum + aVal(j, i) * item (j + 1) of v.
            Set j to j + 1.
        Set item (i + 1) of result to sum.
        Set i to i + 1.
    Return result.

## To mulAtav (n: Int, v: Seq of Float, result: Seq of Float, tmp: Seq of Float) -> Seq of Float:
    Let t be mulAv(n, v, tmp).
    Return mulAtv(n, t, result).

## Main
Let arguments be args().
Let n be parseInt(item 2 of arguments).
Let mutable u be a new Seq of Float.
Let mutable v be a new Seq of Float.
Let mutable tmp be a new Seq of Float.
Let mutable i be 0.
While i is less than n:
    Push 1.0 to u.
    Push 0.0 to v.
    Push 0.0 to tmp.
    Set i to i + 1.
Set i to 0.
While i is less than 10:
    Set v to mulAtav(n, u, v, tmp).
    Set u to mulAtav(n, v, u, tmp).
    Set i to i + 1.
Let mutable vbv be 0.0.
Let mutable vv be 0.0.
Set i to 1.
While i is at most n:
    Set vbv to vbv + item i of u * item i of v.
    Set vv to vv + item i of v * item i of v.
    Set i to i + 1.
Let result be sqrt(vbv / vv).
Show "{result:.9}".

benchmarks.name: Pi (Leibniz Series)
benchmarks.description: Leibniz series for pi. Measures pure FP loop overhead.
benchmarks.logos_source:
## To native args () -> Seq of Text
## To native parseInt (s: Text) -> Int

## Main
Let arguments be args().
Let n be parseInt(item 2 of arguments).
Let mutable sum be 0.0.
Let mutable sign be 1.0.
Let mutable k be 0.
While k is less than n:
    Set sum to sum + sign / (2.0 * k + 1.0).

    Set k to k + 1.

benchmarks.name: GCD Sum
benchmarks.description: GCD sum via Euclidean algorithm. Measures modulo-heavy tight loops.
benchmarks.logos_source:
## To native args () -> Seq of Text
## To native parseInt (s: Text) -> Int

## To gcd (a: Int, b: Int) -> Int:
    Let mutable x be a.
    Let mutable y be b.
    While y is greater than 0:
        Let temp be y.
        Set y to x % y.
        Set x to temp.
    Return x.

## Main
Let arguments be args().
Let n be parseInt(item 2 of arguments).
Let mutable sum be 0.
Let mutable i be 1.
While i is at most n:
    Let mutable j be i.
    While j is at most n:
        Set sum to sum + gcd(i, j).
        Set j to j + 1.
    Set i to i + 1.
Show sum.

benchmarks.name: Collatz Conjecture
benchmarks.description: Collatz step counting. Measures unpredictable branching.
benchmarks.logos_source:
## To native args () -> Seq of Text
## To native parseInt (s: Text) -> Int

## Main
Let arguments be args().
Let n be parseInt(item 2 of arguments).
Let mutable total be 0.
Let mutable i be 1.
While i is at most n:
    Let mutable k be i.
    While k is not 1:
        If k % 2 equals 0:
            Set k to k / 2.
        Otherwise:
            Set k to 3 * k + 1.
        Set total to total + 1.
    Set i to i + 1.
Show total.

benchmarks.name: Primes (Trial Division)
benchmarks.description: Trial division prime counting. Measures nested loops with early exit.
benchmarks.logos_source:
## To native args () -> Seq of Text
## To native parseInt (s: Text) -> Int

## Main
Let arguments be args().
Let n be parseInt(item 2 of arguments).
Let mutable count be 0.
Let mutable i be 2.
While i is at most n:
    Let mutable isPrime be 1.
    Let mutable d be 2.
    While d * d is at most i:
        If i % d equals 0:
            Set isPrime to 0.
            Break.
        Set d to d + 1.
    If isPrime equals 1:
        Set count to count + 1.
    Set i to i + 1.
Show count.

benchmarks.name: Sieve of Eratosthenes
benchmarks.description: Classic prime sieve. Measures indexed array mutation and tight loops.
benchmarks.logos_source:
## To native args () -> Seq of Text
## To native parseInt (s: Text) -> Int

## To sieve (limit: Int) -> Int:
    Let mutable flags be a new Seq of Bool.
    Let mutable i be 0.
    While i is at most limit:
        Push false to flags.
        Set i to i + 1.
    Let mutable count be 0.
    Set i to 2.
    While i is at most limit:
        If item (i + 1) of flags equals false:
            Set count to count + 1.
            Let mutable j be i * i.
            While j is at most limit:
                Set item (j + 1) of flags to true.
                Set j to j + i.
        Set i to i + 1.
    Return count.

## Main
Let arguments be args().
Let limit be parseInt(item 2 of arguments).
Show sieve(limit).

benchmarks.name: Matrix Multiply
benchmarks.description: O(n^3) matrix multiply. Measures cache locality and triple-nested loops.
benchmarks.logos_source:
## To native args () -> Seq of Text
## To native parseInt (s: Text) -> Int

## Main
Let arguments be args().
Let n be parseInt(item 2 of arguments).
Let mutable a be a new Seq of Int.
Let mutable b be a new Seq of Int.
Let mutable c be a new Seq of Int.
Let mutable i be 0.
While i is less than n:
    Let mutable j be 0.
    While j is less than n:
        Push (i * n + j) % 100 to a.
        Push (j * n + i) % 100 to b.
        Push 0 to c.
        Set j to j + 1.
    Set i to i + 1.
Set i to 0.
While i is less than n:
    Let mutable k be 0.
    While k is less than n:
        Let mutable j be 0.
        While j is less than n:
            Let idx be i * n + j + 1.
            Set item idx of c to (item idx of c + item (i * n + k + 1) of a * item (k * n + j + 1) of b) % 1000000007.
            Set j to j + 1.
        Set k to k + 1.
    Set i to i + 1.
Let mutable checksum be 0.
Set i to 1.
While i is at most n * n:
    Set checksum to (checksum + item i of c) % 1000000007.
    Set i to i + 1.
Show checksum.

benchmarks.name: Prefix Sum
benchmarks.description: Sequential prefix sum scan. Measures read-modify-write bandwidth.
benchmarks.logos_source:
## To native args () -> Seq of Text
## To native parseInt (s: Text) -> Int

## Main
Let arguments be args().
Let n be parseInt(item 2 of arguments).
Let mutable arr be a new Seq of Int.
Let mutable seed be 42.
Let mutable i be 0.
While i is less than n:
    Set seed to (seed * 1103515245 + 12345) % 2147483648.
    Push ((seed / 65536) % 32768) % 1000 to arr.
    Set i to i + 1.
Set i to 2.
While i is at most n:
    Set item i of arr to (item i of arr + item (i - 1) of arr) % 1000000007.
    Set i to i + 1.

benchmarks.logos_source:
## To native args () -> Seq of Text
## To native parseInt (s: Text) -> Int

## Main
Let arguments be args().
Let n be parseInt(item 2 of arguments).
Let capacity be n * 5.
Let mutable weights be a new Seq of Int.
Let mutable vals be a new Seq of Int.
Let mutable i be 0.
While i is less than n:
    Push (i * 17 + 3) % 50 + 1 to weights.
    Push (i * 31 + 7) % 100 + 1 to vals.
    Set i to i + 1.
Let cols be capacity + 1.
Let mutable prev be a new Seq of Int.
Let mutable curr be a new Seq of Int.
Set i to 0.
While i is less than cols:
    Push 0 to prev.
    Push 0 to curr.
    Set i to i + 1.
Set i to 0.
While i is less than n:
    Let wi be item (i + 1) of weights.
    Let vi be item (i + 1) of vals.
    Let mutable w be 0.
    While w is at most capacity:
        Set item (w + 1) of curr to item (w + 1) of prev.
        If w is at least wi:
            Let take be item (w - wi + 1) of prev + vi.
            If take is greater than item (w + 1) of curr:
                Set item (w + 1) of curr to take.
        Set w to w + 1.
    Set prev to curr.
    Set i to i + 1.
Show item (capacity + 1) of prev.

benchmarks.name: Fannkuch Redux
benchmarks.description: Fannkuch permutation benchmark. Measures tight array reversal loops.
benchmarks.logos_source:
## To native args () -> Seq of Text
## To native parseInt (s: Text) -> Int

## Main
Let arguments be args().
Let n be parseInt(item 2 of arguments).
Let mutable perm1 be a new Seq of Int.
Let mutable count be a new Seq of Int.
Let mutable i be 0.
While i is less than n:
    Push i to perm1.
    Push 0 to count.
    Set i to i + 1.
Let mutable maxFlips be 0.
Let mutable checksum be 0.
Let mutable permCount be 0.
Let mutable r be n.
Let mutable done be 0.
While done equals 0:
    While r is greater than 1:
        Set item r of count to r.
        Set r to r - 1.
    Let mutable perm be a new Seq of Int.
    Set i to 1.
    While i is at most n:
        Push item i of perm1 to perm.
        Set i to i + 1.
    Let mutable flips be 0.
    While item 1 of perm is not 0:
        Let k be item 1 of perm + 1.
        Let mutable lo be 1.
        Let mutable hi be k.
        While lo is less than hi:
            Let tmp be item lo of perm.
            Set item lo of perm to item hi of perm.
            Set item hi of perm to tmp.
            Set lo to lo + 1.
            Set hi to hi - 1.
        Set flips to flips + 1.
    If flips is greater than maxFlips:
        Set maxFlips to flips.
    If permCount % 2 equals 0:
        Set checksum to checksum + flips.
    Otherwise:
        Set checksum to checksum - flips.
    Set permCount to permCount + 1.
    Set done to 1.
    While done equals 1:
        If r equals n:
            Set done to 2.
        Otherwise:
            Let perm0 be item 1 of perm1.
            Set i to 1.
            While i is at most r:
                Set item i of perm1 to item (i + 1) of perm1.
                Set i to i + 1.
            Set item (r + 1) of perm1 to perm0.
            Set item (r + 1) of count to (item (r + 1) of count) - 1.
            If item (r + 1) of count is greater than 0:
                Set done to 0.
            Otherwise:
                Set r to r + 1.
Show checksum.
Show maxFlips.

benchmarks.name: Binary Trees
benchmarks.description: Recursive tree creation and checksum. Measures allocation pressure.
benchmarks.logos_source:
## To native args () -> Seq of Text
## To native parseInt (s: Text) -> Int

## To makeCheck (depth: Int) -> Int:
    If depth equals 0:
        Return 1.
    Return 1 + makeCheck(depth - 1) + makeCheck(depth - 1).

## Main
Let arguments be args().
Let n be parseInt(item 2 of arguments).
Let minDepth be 4.
Let mutable maxDepth be n.
If minDepth + 2 is greater than maxDepth:
    Set maxDepth to minDepth + 2.

Let stretchCheck be makeCheck(maxDepth + 1).
Show "stretch tree of depth " + (maxDepth + 1) + " check: " + stretchCheck.

Let longLived be makeCheck(maxDepth).

Let mutable depth be minDepth.
While depth is at most maxDepth:
    Let mutable iterations be 1.
    Let mutable p be 0.
    While p is less than maxDepth - depth + minDepth:
        Set iterations to iterations * 2.
        Set p to p + 1.
    Let mutable totalCheck be 0.
    Let mutable i be 0.
    While i is less than iterations:
        Set totalCheck to totalCheck + makeCheck(depth).
        Set i to i + 1.
    Show "" + iterations + " trees of depth " + depth + " check: " + totalCheck.
    Set depth to depth + 2.
Show "long lived tree of depth " + maxDepth + " check: " + longLived.

benchmarks.name: Graph BFS
benchmarks.description: BFS on generated graph. Measures queue operations and random access.
benchmarks.logos_source:
## To native args () -> Seq of Text
## To native parseInt (s: Text) -> Int

## Main
Let arguments be args().
Let n be parseInt(item 2 of arguments).
Let mutable adj be a new Seq of Int.
Let mutable adjStarts be a new Seq of Int.
Let mutable adjCounts be a new Seq of Int.
Let mutable i be 0.
While i is less than n:
    Push i * 5 to adjStarts.
    Push 0 to adjCounts.
    Push 0 to adj. Push 0 to adj. Push 0 to adj. Push 0 to adj. Push 0 to adj.
    Set i to i + 1.
Let mutable primes be a new Seq of Int.
Push 31 to primes. Push 37 to primes. Push 41 to primes. Push 43 to primes. Push 47 to primes.
Let mutable offsets be a new Seq of Int.
Push 7 to offsets. Push 13 to offsets. Push 17 to offsets. Push 23 to offsets. Push 29 to offsets.
Let mutable p be 1.
While p is at most 5:
    Set i to 0.
    While i is less than n:
        Let neighbor be (i * item p of primes + item p of offsets) % n.
        If neighbor is not i:
            Let start be item (i + 1) of adjStarts.
            Let cnt be item (i + 1) of adjCounts.
            Set item (start + cnt + 1) of adj to neighbor.
            Set item (i + 1) of adjCounts to cnt + 1.
        Set i to i + 1.
    Set p to p + 1.
Let mutable queue be a new Seq of Int.
Let mutable dist be a new Seq of Int.
Set i to 0.
While i is less than n:
    Push 0 - 1 to dist.
    Set i to i + 1.
Push 0 to queue.
Set item 1 of dist to 0.
Let mutable front be 1.
While front is at most length of queue:
    Let v be item front of queue.
    Let start be item (v + 1) of adjStarts.
    Let cnt be item (v + 1) of adjCounts.
    Let mutable e be 0.
    While e is less than cnt:
        Let u be item (start + e + 1) of adj.
        If item (u + 1) of dist equals 0 - 1:
            Set item (u + 1) of dist to item (v + 1) of dist + 1.
            Push u to queue.
        Set e to e + 1.
    Set front to front + 1.
Let mutable reachable be 0.
Let mutable totalDist be 0.
Set i to 0.
While i is less than n:
    If item (i + 1) of dist is at least 0:
        Set reachable to reachable + 1.
        Set totalDist to totalDist + item (i + 1) of dist.
    Set i to i + 1.
Show "" + reachable + " " + totalDist.

benchmarks.name: Naive String Search
benchmarks.description: Naive O(nm) string search. Measures character-level access and inner loop.
benchmarks.logos_source:
## To native args () -> Seq of Text
## To native parseInt (s: Text) -> Int

## Main
Let arguments be args().
Let n be parseInt(item 2 of arguments).
Let mutable text be "".
Let mutable pos be 0.
While pos is less than n:
    If pos is greater than 0:
        If pos % 1000 equals 0:
            If pos + 5 is at most n:
                Set text to text + "XXXXX".
                Set pos to pos + 5.
    If pos is less than n:
        Let mutable ch be "a".
        If pos % 5 equals 1:
            Set ch to "b".
        If pos % 5 equals 2:
            Set ch to "c".
        If pos % 5 equals 3:
            Set ch to "d".
        If pos % 5 equals 4:
            Set ch to "e".
        Set text to text + ch.
        Set pos to pos + 1.
Let needle be "XXXXX".
Let needleLen be 5.
Let textLen be length of text.
Let mutable count be 0.
Let mutable i be 1.
While i is at most textLen - needleLen + 1:
    Let mutable match be 1.
    Let mutable j be 0.
    While j is less than needleLen:
        If item (i + j) of text is not item (j + 1) of needle:
            Set match to 0.
            Set j to needleLen.
        Set j to j + 1.
    If match equals 1:
        Set count to count + 1.
    Set i to i + 1.
Show count.
